next_sequence += str(count) + current_sequence[i]\n                i += 1\n            # Update the current sequence to the next sequence\n            current_sequence = next_sequence\n        \n        return current_sequence\n```\n\nThis solution generates the count-and-say sequence iteratively by building each sequence from the previous one. It uses a while loop to count consecutive characters and constructs the next sequence by appending the count followed by the character.", "estimated_date": 1438905600000}